content:
Venture capital firm Haun Ventures, known for its crypto focus, has hired Suzanne Kim to handle investor relations, the Wall Street Journal <a href="https://www.wsj.com/amp/articles/crypto-focused-haun-ventures-hires-private-equity-veteran-e33eeff7" data-v-f87c67ca="">reported</a>, citing the company.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
Kim joins Haun as a partner. She was most recently a managing director at Hellman &amp; Friedman, and was previously a vice president at TPG Capital.&nbsp;
